Default Thread is Main Thread. Jab tu Java program run karta hai, JVM automatically ek main thread create karta hai jo main() method ko execute karta hai. Agar tu new threads create karta hai, to wo main thread ke alawa execute honge.

Ways to Create a New Thread in Java

1. Extending Thread class
Apni class ko java.lang.Thread class se extend karke run() method override karte hai. Object banane ke baad .start() call karte hai jo naya thread create karke run() ko execute karta hai.
Limitation: Java single inheritance support karta hai, to agar Thread extend kar liya to koi aur class extend nahi kar sakte.
2. Implementing Runnable interface
Runnable interface implement karke run() method define karte hai. Fir uska object Thread class ke constructor mein pass karke .start() call karte hai.
✔ Preferred way — kyunki interface implement karne se doosri class bhi extend kar sakte hai (inheritance flexibility milti hai).
✔ Better design — task (Runnable) aur thread (Thread) ko separate karta hai, "separation of concerns" follow hota hai.
3. Implementing Callable interface
Callable<V> interface use karte hai jab thread se return value chahiye ya checked exception throw karni ho (Runnable ka run() kuch return nahi karta aur checked exception throw nahi kar sakta).
Callable ka call() method value return karta hai, jo Future object ke through mila jata hai. Ye ExecutorService ke saath use hota hai.
